#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:1
msgid "Billing settings (MR/MRS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:4
msgid ""
"Configure Resthome's MR/MRS settings tab for a nursing home (MR/MRS): "
"automatic billing, journals, Cc accreditation, absences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:8
msgid "Where are the MR/MRS billing settings located?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:9
msgid ""
"In Settings > MR/MRS. The tab is only visible to MR/MRS managers. It gathers "
"automatic billing, journals, facility accreditation, split billing and "
"absence management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:11
msgid "Should automatic billing refresh be enabled?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:12
msgid ""
"Yes, that is the recommended value. When enabled, it keeps every open billing"
" period up to date as soon as any data changes: supplement, absence, end of "
"stay, change of room or health insurance fund, mid-month admission. Only "
"disable it if you prefer to recalculate solely by clicking \"Refresh\" on the"
" period."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:14
msgid ""
"What is the difference between the INAMI Journal and the Resident Journal?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:15
msgid ""
"The INAMI Journal receives the invoices for the insurer share (sent via "
"eFact); the Resident Journal receives those for the resident share "
"(accommodation and supplements). These are two sales journals of your "
"facility, preferably kept separate for clear accounting tracking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:17
msgid "When should the Cc accreditation be ticked?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:18
msgid ""
"Only if your facility holds the accreditation that authorizes billing the "
"Ccoma coma lump sum. Without this accreditation, a resident classified as "
"Ccoma cannot be billed via eFact; accommodation, however, is still billed. "
"This is a facility-specific value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:20
msgid "Does enabling split billing install a module?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:21
msgid ""
"Yes. Ticking \"Split billing (maintenance debtors)\" installs the "
"corresponding module; unticking it uninstalls it. Enable it if maintenance "
"debtors share the resident portion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:23
msgid "What is the Katz activity assignee for?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:24
msgid ""
"It is the user to whom Resthome assigns the \"New Katz required\" activity "
"when a readmission after hospitalization exceeds 30 days. If the field is "
"empty, the activity goes to the current user if they are clinical, otherwise "
"to the first head nurse, nurse or doctor found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:27
msgid ""
"The **MR/MRS** settings tab gathers the parameters that drive the **billing**"
" of your nursing home: invoice generation, accounting journals, facility "
"accreditation and absence management. You configure them **once**, then they "
"only change at the margins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:32
msgid ""
"You will find them under **Settings > MR/MRS**. The tab is only visible to "
"**MR/MRS managers**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid "eHealth secrets are configured elsewhere"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:38
msgid ""
"The **eHealth certificate (.p12)**, the **CIN license** and the health-"
"insurer connection credentials are **not** found in this tab, but in the "
"**[eHealth](../ehealth/index.md)** configuration. This tab contains **no "
"secret data**; you enter neither password nor key here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:44
msgid "Automatic billing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:46
msgid ""
"This block decides **how** and **when** invoices are produced, and whether "
"open periods keep themselves up to date on their own."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:75
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:92
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:111
msgid "Setting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:75
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:92
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:111
msgid "What it does"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:75
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:92
#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:111
msgid "Recommended value (MR/MRS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid "**Automatic billing**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid ""
"Automatically generates the monthly stay invoices, without going through the "
"manual cycle. Disabled by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid ""
"Depending on your organization; often left **disabled** in favor of the "
"manual cycle (generate → invoice), which gives more control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid "**Billing day**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid ""
"Day of the month on which automatic invoices are generated (only visible if "
"automatic billing is enabled)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid ""
"**1** (start of the month) by default; adjust according to your organization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid "**Automatic billing refresh**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid ""
"Keeps every open period up to date as soon as any data changes: supplement, "
"absence, end of stay, change of room or health insurance fund, mid-month "
"admission."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:35
msgid "**Enabled** — recommended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
msgid "Automatic refresh and the \"Refresh\" button"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:58
msgid ""
"With refresh **enabled**, adding a supplement or an absence is reflected on "
"the period on its own: you generally have nothing to do. The period's "
"**\"Refresh\"** button remains available for a full on-demand recalculation. "
"See [Bill a month](../facturation/facturer-un-mois.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:64
msgid "Billing journals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:66
msgid ""
"Resthome issues **two streams** of invoices: the **insurer share** "
"(dependency lump sum, sent to the insuring body via eFact) and the **resident"
" share** (accommodation and supplements). Each stream goes into its own sales"
" journal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
msgid "**INAMI Journal**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
msgid ""
"Sales journal that receives the invoices for the **insurer share** "
"(dependency lump sum sent via eFact)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
msgid "A sales journal of your facility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
msgid "**Resident Journal**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
msgid ""
"Sales journal that receives the invoices for the **resident share** "
"(accommodation and supplements)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:55
msgid "A sales journal **separate** from the previous one (recommended)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:75
msgid "Facility-specific value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:78
msgid ""
"These two journals depend on **your chart of accounts**. Choose existing "
"**sales** journals. Separating them (INAMI on one side, resident on the "
"other) makes reconciliation and per-payer tracking easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:83
msgid "Facility accreditation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:85
msgid ""
"Some federal lump sums require a **specific accreditation** of the facility. "
"This is the case for the **coma (Ccoma)** lump sum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:75
msgid "**Cc accreditation (coma lump sum)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:75
msgid ""
"Tick if the facility holds the accreditation allowing it to bill the "
"**Ccoma** coma lump sum. Without it, a resident classified as Ccoma is "
"**not** billable via eFact (neither regional nor federal); accommodation is "
"still billed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:75
msgid "Tick **only** if your facility is accredited."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:92
msgid "Not to be confused with the lump-sum amount"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:95
msgid ""
"The ordinary **dependency lump sum** is the **same amount** for all Katz "
"categories; the category is used to **declare the profile** to the health "
"insurance fund, not to set the amount (see [The INAMI lump "
"sum](../facturation/forfait-inami.md)). The Cc accreditation, for its part, "
"concerns only the **special case of the coma lump sum**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:102
msgid "Optional features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:104
msgid ""
"An additional module is installed directly from the settings, by ticking a "
"checkbox."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:92
msgid "**Split billing (maintenance debtors)**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:92
msgid ""
"Splits the resident share of the monthly invoice among several debtors, each "
"paying a percentage. Ticking this box **installs** the module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:92
msgid "Enable it **if** maintenance debtors share the resident share."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:111
msgid "What the checkbox does"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:114
msgid ""
"Ticking installs the module and unticking uninstalls it (standard module "
"convention). Once enabled, the split is configured per resident. See "
"[Maintenance debtors](../facturation/split-billing.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:119
msgid "Absence management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:121
msgid ""
"The **presence day** rules (noon rule, hospitalization, leave) are **built "
"into** Resthome and are not configured here. Only the **assignee** of a "
"follow-up activity is configurable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:111
msgid "**Katz activity assignee**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:111
msgid ""
"User to whom the \"New Katz required\" activity is assigned when a hospital "
"readmission exceeds **30 days**. If empty: current user (if clinical), "
"otherwise the first head nurse, nurse or doctor found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:111
msgid "The **head nurse** (or the care manager)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:129
msgid "Why 30 days?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/configuration/reglages-facturation.md:132
msgid ""
"A readmission after more than 30 days of hospitalization requires a **new "
"Katz assessment**. The assigned activity acts as a reminder. See [Absences "
"and hospitalizations](../facturation/absences.md)."
msgstr ""

